m/rwf2/Rocket/issues/1790#issuecomment-888498521","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/1790","id":888498521,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAzqMt8409WlZ","user":{"login":"jebrosen","id":7102588,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcxMDI1ODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7102588?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen","html_url":"https://github.com/jebrosen","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-07-28T17:45:28Z","updated_at":"2021-07-28T17:45:28Z","body":"> * mysql_async provides the Queryable trait to abstract over a connection and a transaction. The trait is only implemented for a value, not for a mutable reference.\r\n> * Connection<T> from db_pools only implements deref and deref_mut. It's not possible to unwrap it into its inner value.\r\n\r\nCan you show a short example of something you want to be able to write today but can't because of this missing functionality? I'm not sure I understand what the proposed change accomplishes, since `DerefMut` *should* already provide access to any methods that take `&mut self`.","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/comments/888498521/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"jebrosen","id":7102588,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcxMDI1ODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7102588?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen","html_url":"https://github.com/jebrosen","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/comments/888856218","html_url":"https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/1790#issuecomment-888856218","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/1790","id":888856218,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAzqMt840-t6a","user":{"login":"roy-ganz","id":42205143,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQyMjA1MTQz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/42205143?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz","html_url":"https://github.com/roy-ganz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-07-29T07:02:23Z","updated_at":"2021-07-29T07:02:23Z","body":"This is my situation:\r\n```\r\n// ...\r\n#[get(\"/<id>?<query..>\")]\r\npub async fn get( id: u64, conn: Connection<DbConn>, cache: &State<Cache>){\r\n    let mut toql =  MySqlAsync::from( ???, &cache);    \r\n    //                                 ^-- Here I get sqeezed between Rocket and mysql_async, see below\r\n    \r\n    let u = toql.load_one( query!(User, \"*, id eq ?\", id)).await?;\r\n    Ok(Json(u))\r\n}\r\n// ...\r\n```\r\nThe backend driver (here MySqlAsync) must be able to wrap a connection or transaction. On the `toql` object the ORM functions can then be called.\r\nThe Problem: From `Rocket` I can only get a `&mut DnConn`. But `mysql_async` implements the [Queryable](https://docs.rs/mysql_async/0.28.0/mysql_async/prelude/trait.Queryable.html) trait only for `DbConn` (value). \r\n\r\nRight now, I have solved it like this:\r\n```\r\n//...\r\n  let mut toql =  MySqlAsync::from( conn.into_inner(), &cache);    \r\n//...\r\n```\r\nI cloned the Rocket repo and added the `into_inner()` function to `Connection`, so that I can unwrap it.\r\n- Not ergonomic for users\r\n- However I think unwrapping `Connection` should still be allowed to get a value, for the usual Rust tradeoff (Less troubles than &mut, but also less performance)\r\n\r\nPersonally I preferred this\r\n```\r\n//...\r\n  let mut toql =  MySqlAsync::from(&mut conn , &cache);    \r\n//...\r\n```\r\n- Better ergonomics\r\n- Needs [Queryable](https://docs.rs/mysql_async/0.28.0/mysql_async/prelude/trait.Queryable.html) implemented on [&mut Conn](https://docs.rs/mysql_async/0.28.0/mysql_async/struct.Conn.html)\r\n- More coding work than solution above\r\n\r\nFrankly, either way, I don't really mind. But without a solution I cannot depend my crates on public dependencies, which blocks the upcoming beta release. \r\nIt's my last day before vacation today. I will have time to work on this in the beginning of september. So there is no rush.\r\n\r\nHave a nice summertime.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/comments/888856218/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"roy-ganz","id":42205143,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQyMjA1MTQz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/42205143?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz","html_url":"https://github.com/roy-ganz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"actor":{"login":"roy-ganz","id":42205143,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQyMjA1MTQz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/42205143?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz","html_url":"https://github.com/roy-ganz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/roy-ganz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscrip