ls) for async databases. MySql is officially supported through sqlx. However you provide a pool yourself, so I try to use your Pool and keep sqlx out. I compiles on my machine. However I have some friction:\r\n- Rockets [Connection](https://github.com/SergioBenitez/Rocket/blob/master/contrib/db_pools/lib/src/database.rs) struct only allows deref /deref_mut to the inner connection.\r\n- Queryable is only implemented for Conn. Looking at the methods, it should be possible to implement it for &mut Conn too.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think about that?","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blackbeam/mysql_async/issues/165/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blackbeam/mysql_async/issues/165/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/comments/890031056","html_url":"https://github.com/rwf2/Rocket/issues/1790#issuecomment-890031056","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/1790","id":890031056,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAzqMt841DMvQ","user":{"login":"jebrosen","id":7102588,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcxMDI1ODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7102588?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen","html_url":"https://github.com/jebrosen","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jebrosen/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-07-30T17:05:22Z","updated_at":"2021-07-30T17:05:22Z","body":"Okay, I think I understand the mismatch now. This problem is not relevant for all engines, but might affect a few more besides `mysql_async`:\r\n\r\n* The equivalent `sqlx` methods take an `E: Executor`, which is implemented for references to connections or transactions, and therefore doesn't have this problem\r\n* The equivalent `diesel` methods (not relevant, but for comparison's sake) take an `&Connection`, and wouldn't have this problem\r\n* `tokio-postgres` has a similar trait, `GenericClient`, which may have the same problem\r\n* `redis` has a similar trait, `ConnectionLike`, which may have the same problem\r\n\r\nThere are a few different kinds of solutions here:\r\n\r\n* Your APIs might be able to use e.g. `&mut X where X: Queryable` instead, similarly to `diesel`. This may not be as ergonomic as the other approaches, but it should be doable without modifying either `rocket` or `mysql_async`\r\n* `mysql_async` could implement `Queryable for &mut Q where Q: Queryable`, along the same lines as traits such as `std::io::{Read,Write}`, `serde::{Serialize,Deserialize}` which make use cases including this one more ergonomic\r\n* `rocket_db_pools` could add an `into_inner()` method. I actually don't see any immediate problems with doing this today; my only hesitation is that it would not play nicely with an `impl Drop for Connection` should we want to add one in the future. I don't expect that we would need that, so in my eyes this is probably worth doing.","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/comments/890031056/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"jebrosen","id":710